Government is stepping up its rollout campaign with the opening of private mass vaccine sites. JOHANNESBURG - Dis-Chem and other pharmacies from this week are administering the Pfizer vaccine on their premises. But the public still needs to use the government registration process to book their spot. READ: COVID-19 Vaccine | Concerns raised over rollout At the moment only persons aged 60 and over can get the jab. eNCA's Heidi Giokos reports from the Medicare Pharmacy in Douglasdale, Johannesburg.